  "Regulator Statement" : "HEARING PANEL DECISION RENDERED JULY 2, 2012 WHEREIN LANE IS BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY FINRA MEMBER IN ANY CAPACITY FOR FAILING TO ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN REASONABLE WRITTEN SUPERVISORY PROCEDURES REGARDING MARKUPS AND FAILING TO SUPERVISE A REPRESENTATIVE'S MARKUP ACTIVITIES APPROPRIATELY. LANE IS ALSO BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY FINRA MEMBER IN ANY CAPACITY FOR FAILURE TO PROVIDE INFORMATION AND DOCUMENTS IN VIOLATION OF FINRA RULE 8210 UNTIL AFTER A NOTICE OF SUSPENSION WAS ISSUED. LANE IS ORDERED TO PAY RESTITUTION OF $317,030.70 TO CUSTOMERS, JOINTLY AND SEVERALLY, AND TO PAY COSTS OF $4,625.25, JOINTLY AND SEVERALLY. APPEALED TO THE NAC ON JULY 25, 2012. NAC DECISION RENDERED DECEMBER 26, 2013 WHEREIN LANE IS BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY FINRA MEMBER IN ANY PRINCIPAL OR SUPERVISORY CAPACITY FOR HIS SUPERVISORY VIOLATIONS AND SUSPENDED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY FINRA MEMBER IN ANY CAPACITY FOR TWO YEARS AND FINED $25,000 FOR HIS FAILURES TO RESPOND. THE NAC VACATED THE RESTITUTION ORDER IMPOSED BY THE HEARING PANEL. LANE IS ORDERED TO PAY $4,282.65 IN HEARING COSTS, JOINTLY AND SEVERALLY. THE BAR IS EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY. APPEALED TO THE SEC ON JANUARY 28, 2014. SEC RELEASE 34-74269, FEBRUARY 13, 2015: THE SANCTIONS WERE SUSTAINED BY THE SEC FOLLOWING APPEAL OF A NATIONAL ADJUDICATORY COUNCIL (NAC) DECISION. THE SANCTIONS WERE BASED ON FINDINGS THAT LANE PREPARED DEFICIENT WSPS REGARDING INTERPOSITIONING OR ANY PROCEDURES ON HOW TO MONITOR FOR EXCESSIVE MARKUPS. THE FINDINGS STATED THAT LANE WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR SUPERVISING A REPRESENTATIVE'S ACTIVITIES BUT FAILED TO REASONABLY SUPERVISE THE REPRESENTATIVE WITH A VIEW TO PREVENTING VIOLATIONS OF SECTION 10(B) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 AND RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER. DESPITE THE PRESENCE OF RED FLAGS, LANE DID NOT RESPOND IN A REASONABLE MANNER AND HIS QUESTIONING OF THE MARK-UPS DID NOT SATISFY HIS SUPERVISORY OBLIGATIONS. THE FINDINGS ALSO STATED THAT LANE FAILED TO TIMELY RESPOND TO FINRA REQUESTS FOR INFORMATION IN A TIMELY MANNER. THE DECISION BECAME FINAL APRIL 14, 2015."
